thread.title: Iowa football's toughest critics? Two adorable kids
thread.title_full: Iowa football's toughest critics? Two adorable kids

author: desmoinesregister.com
title: Iowa football's toughest critics? Two adorable kids
text:
Iowa coach Kirk Ferentz, in his 17th season, has Hawkeyes winning again. (Photo: Jerry Lai/USA Today)
Iowa is 7-0 and ranked No. 12 in the AP Top 25. They are one of the 14 FBS teams still unbeaten .
According to ESPN's Power Index, Iowa is huge favorites in four of its last five regular-season games. The lone team expected to beat Iowa? ESPN says the Hawkeyes have only a 47 percent chance of winning the regular-season finale against nemesis Nebraska.
In some ways, Iowa is in some impressive company:
Good line from Iowa football notes: Of 14 undefeated FBS teams, Hawkeyes' SOS is ranked 3rd behind Utah and LSU.
— Chad Leistikow (@ChadLeistikow) October 21, 2015 FYI: Alabama and Iowa are the only teams with two Top 25 road victories this season. https://t.co/N1S4cvbwN7
— Rick Brown (@ByRickBrown) October 19, 2015 However, not everyone is buying that Iowa is deserving of an undefeated season, especially Alabama fan and Tosh.O writer Joe Borden and his (Auburn clad???) children in this satire video.
